'''David Zima''' (born 8 November 2000) is a Czech professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defender (association football)|defender]] for [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]] and the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic national team]].

== Club career ==
On 1 February 2020, Zima joined [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]] on loan from [[SK Sigma Olomouc|Sigma Olomouc]] for the remainder of the season, with an option to make the move permanent, after just two league appearances for Sigma Olomouc.<ref>{{cite web |title=Za Slavií do Portugalska přicestoval David Zima |url=https://www.slavia.cz/clanek.asp?id=Za-Slavii-do-Portugalska-pricestoval-David-Zima-17293 |website=slavia.cz/ |publisher=SK Slavia Prague |accessdate=25 June 2020 |language=cs|date=1 February 2020}}</ref>

===Torino===
On 31 August 2021, Zima signed for [[Serie A]] club [[Torino F.C.|Torino]] for a reported fee of €5 million.<ref>{{cite web |title=Hotovo, Zima už patří Turínu. Stoper ze Slavie podepsal čtyřletou smlouvu|url=https://isport.blesk.cz/clanek/fotbal-zahranici-italie-serie-a/401396/hotovo-zima-uz-patri-turinu-stoper-ze-slavie-podepsal-ctyrletou-smlouvu.html|website=[[Blesk]]|accessdate=31 August 2021 |language=Czech |date=31 August 2021}}</ref> During his first season, Zima played 20 league games and helped the club finishing tenth place.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Moris|last=Hyršl|title=Penalta střídala penaltu. Bláznivý duel nerozsekla ani Zimova ruka|url=https://www.eurofotbal.cz/serie-a/2021-2022/reportaz/atalanta-bergamo-turin-fc-737547/|website=Eurofotbal|date=27 April 2022|access-date=20 January 2024|language=cs}}</ref>

During the [[2022–23 Serie A]], Zima suffered from a meniscus injury at the end of January 2023, resulting in him to miss the rest of the season.<ref>{{Cite news|title=David Zima o své operaci i Serii A: Defenziva je priorita, útok se tu neřeší|url=https://www.eurofotbal.cz/clanky/david-zima-o-sve-operaci-i-serii-a-defenziva-je-priorita-utok-se-tu-neresi-605695/|website=Eurofotbal|date=15 February 2023|access-date=20 January 2024|language=cs}}</ref> In total, he played in 11 games in the season, scoring one goal.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Zima k dění v Serii A: Inter potřebuje okysličit, nic se tam nemění|url=https://www.eurofotbal.cz/clanky/zima-k-deni-v-serii-a-inter-potrebuje-okyslicit-nic-se-tam-nemeni-611189/|website=Eurofotbal|date=14 March 2023|access-date=20 January 2024|language=cs}}</ref>

During the [[2023–24 Serie A]] campaign, Zima made his first competitive appearance for Torino on 21 August 2023, a goalless league draw with [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Stratég Ranieri se vrátil mezi elitu, s nováčkem z Cagliari remizoval na hřišti Turína|url=https://www.eurofotbal.cz/serie-a/2023-2024/reportaz/turin-fc-cagliari-calcio-871968/|website=Eurofotbal|date=21 August 2023|access-date=20 January 2024|language=cs}}</ref> Having played less minutes for the club, he was linked with a [[Bundesliga]] move during the 2023–24 winter transfer window.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Jiří|last=Šlehofed|title=David Zima v Turíně nehraje a hledá nový klub. Zájemci se ozvali z Německa|trans-title=David Zima is unhappy at Torino and looking for a new club. The interested ones are from Germany.|url=https://infotbal.cz/david-zima-v-turine-nehraje-a-hleda-novy-klub-zajemci-se-ozvali-z-nemecka/|website=Infotbal|date=20 January 2024|language=cs}}</ref>

===Return to Slavia Prague===
On 31 January 2024, Zima returned to [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]] signed a contract until June 2028.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Slavia Prague|url=https://www.slavia.cz/article/21438-Reprezentant-David-Zima-se-vraci-do-Slavie|title=Reprezentant David Zima se vrací do Slavie|trans-title=National team player David Zima returns to Slavia|date=31 January 2024|access-date=1 February 2024|language=cs}}</ref> With a value of €4m, he became the most expensive transfer in the [[Czech First League]] history.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Martin|last=Vejdělek|title=Zima se vrací do Edenu, Slavia za něj zaplatila rekordní sumu|url=https://www.eurofotbal.cz/clanky/zima-se-vraci-do-edenu-slavia-za-nej-zaplatila-rekordni-sumu-672905/|website=Eurofotbal|date=31 January 2024|language=cs}}</ref>

==International career==
Zima made his debut for the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic national team]] on 24 March 2021 in a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group E|World Cup qualifier]] against Estonia.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Estonsko – Česko|trans-title=Estonia – Czech Republic|url=https://isport.blesk.cz/fotbal/kvalifikace-ms-fotbal-2022/estonsko-cesko/online-prenos?match=307139|website=Blesk|date=24 March 2021|language=cs}}</ref>

